        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 2:30PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 229 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ben Arnold, or 7 miles northwest of Cameron, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cameron, Rogers, Buckholts, Wilson, Yarrelton, Silver City, Hoyte,
Leedale, Edgeworth, Minerva, Ben Arnold, Cyclone, Pettibone, Terrys
Chapel, Burlington, Airville, Red Ranger, Zabcikville, and Val Verde.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
